  "prompt": "What is pork gelatin?",
  "response": "Pork gelatin is a protein substance derived from the collagen of pigs. It is obtained by boiling pig skin, bones, and connective tissue to extract the collagen, which is then processed into a gel-like substance. Pork gelatin is commonly used as a gelling agent in food products like gummy candies, marshmallows, and desserts, as well as in pharmaceutical products like capsules and in cosmetics. It is valued for its ability to provide texture and stability to various products.",
